# Clock hour format (extension)

Tabocalypse has a **global** 12-hour / 24-hour preference (`clockHourFormat`, optional `clockHourFormatAuto` in [`apps/extension/lib/settings.ts`](../../apps/extension/lib/settings.ts)). Users set it from the **Clock** widget toggles; alarms and other HUD surfaces must honor the same effective value.

## Resolve the effective format

- Use **`resolveEffectiveClockHourFormat`** from [`apps/extension/lib/locale-units.ts`](../../apps/extension/lib/locale-units.ts) — do not read `clockHourFormat` alone when `clockHourFormatAuto` may apply.
- In the new-tab app, memoize once (same pattern as `effectiveWeatherTemperatureUnit`) and pass the result into formatters / widgets.

## Format user-visible local times

- **Do not** call bare **`Date#toLocaleString()`** or **`Date#toLocaleTimeString()`** for extension UI that shows a clock time — browser locale defaults ignore Tabocalypse’s setting (e.g. US locale forces PM even when the user chose 24-hour).
- Pass explicit **`Intl`** options with **`hour12: hourFormat === "12h"`** (and matching `hour` / `minute` / `second` digit options).
- Use **`getNavigatorFormattingLocale()`** for the locale argument unless a caller already has a HUD display locale.

### Shared helpers (prefer these)

| Surface | Helper / pattern |
|--------|-------------------|
| Scheduled alarms list | **`formatAlarmScheduledLabel`** in [`apps/extension/lib/alarm-datetime.ts`](../../apps/extension/lib/alarm-datetime.ts) |
| Live clock widget | **`toLocaleTimeString(locale, { hour12: hourFormat === "12h", timeZone, … })`** — see [`clock-widget.tsx`](../../apps/extension/components/built-in/clock-widget.tsx); `timeZone` comes from shared HUD coordinates via [`resolveTimezoneFromCoords`](../../apps/extension/lib/resolve-timezone-from-coords.ts) (see [hud-shared-geo-location.mdc](hud-shared-geo-location.mdc)) |

When adding a **new** user-visible timestamp, add or extend a colocated helper in `lib/` (and a `*.test.ts` case) instead of inlining another one-off `toLocaleString`.

## `datetime-local` inputs (exception)

**`<input type="datetime-local">`** display is controlled by the **browser/OS**; you cannot force 12h vs 24h in that control. Store/edit values with **`formatDatetimeLocalFromDate`** (always 24h-style `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm` internally). Only **read-only labels** (lists, toasts, notifications copy) must follow the global clock setting.

## Tests

- Extend **`alarm-datetime.test.ts`** (or the relevant `*.test.ts`) when changing alarm/time formatters.
- Assert both **`"12h"`** and **`"24h"`** for at least one fixed `Date` + locale (e.g. 15:15 → `15:15:00` vs `03:15:00 PM` under `en-US`).
